<br>
Line 1: Welcome to EverQuest!<br>
Line 2: You have entered Butcherblock Mountains.<br>
Line 3: So_and_so tells you, "Can you take me to EC plz."<br>
<br>
I've recently begun to actively seek exp on my druid again, and I've found that the creation of a couple keys has helped my frustrastion level. The most often used one reads: /r Sorry, but I am not available for gates right now. I can't recall a time when I've received any response but an "Ok, thanks" from someone using that reply. It may seem like a lazy method, but I hate to ignore people, and I'm a fairly poor typist, so it allows me to reply to requests even under hectic conditions.<br>
